description:
In bridge-jmap/src/bridge.rs, the relay event handler only processes ClientEvent::Message notifications where notif.method == rpc_methods::DELIVER:

  ClientEvent::Message(notif) => {
      if notif.method == rpc_methods::DELIVER {
          handle_nie_deliver(...).await;
      }
      // BROADCAST is not handled
  }

BROADCAST is the method used for MLS-encrypted group messages (the primary message type once a group is established). The bridge completely ignores all BROADCAST notifications. This means:

1. Any group chat message (the standard MLS-encrypted path) is silently dropped by the bridge -- it never reaches JMAP.
2. Only legacy DELIVER messages (unencrypted peer-to-peer) are forwarded.

If the relay session has an MLS group active (which daemon.rs encourages), the bridge forwards nothing. This is a correctness bug: the bridge claims to forward nie chat to JMAP but silently drops the majority of traffic when MLS is in use.
